# Invite Code System & Admin Management

## Overview

The invite code system restricts user signups to invitation-only. Administrators generate one-time-use invite codes that users must provide during signup. This replaces the previous direct user creation flow.

## Architecture

### Backend Components

#### Invite Codes Module
- [apps/api/src/app/invite-codes](mdc:apps/api/src/app/invite-codes) - Main invite codes module
  - [invite-codes.entity.ts](mdc:apps/api/src/app/invite-codes/entities/invite-code.entity.ts) - Database entity
  - [invite-codes.service.ts](mdc:apps/api/src/app/invite-codes/invite-codes.service.ts) - Business logic
  - [invite-codes.controller.ts](mdc:apps/api/src/app/invite-codes/invite-codes.controller.ts) - API endpoints
  - [invite-code.guard.ts](mdc:apps/api/src/app/invite-codes/guards/invite-code.guard.ts) - Guard for validating codes

#### Database Schema
- [apps/api/src/db/migrations/1766546648442-invite-codes.ts](mdc:apps/api/src/db/migrations/1766546648442-invite-codes.ts) - Migration file
- Table: `invite_codes`
  - `id` (UUID, primary key)
  - `code` (UUID, unique) - The actual invite code
  - `created_by` (UUID, foreign key to users) - Admin who created it
  - `created_at` (timestamp)
  - `is_active` (boolean) - Whether code is still valid
  - `consumed_by` (UUID, nullable, foreign key to users) - User who used it
  - `consumed_at` (timestamp, nullable) - When it was consumed

